
[1]cashew-nut

   CASHEW-NUT, n. A tree of the West-Indies, Anacardium, bearing a
   kidney-shaped nut. The fruit is as large as an orange, and full of an
   acid juice, which is often used to make punch. To the apex of this
   fruit grows a nut, of the size of a hares kidney, the shell of which is
   hard, and the kernel, which is sweet, is covered with a thin film.
     __________________________________________________________________

